description: The underlying elliptic curve is brainpoolP256t1.
The message digest for hashing the input is SHA-256.
Signatures consists of two parts r,s where r,s are encoded as unsigned, bigendian, fixed-length byte arrays.

references.title: Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC) Brainpool Standard Curves and Curve Generation

Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

SpecialHash.desc: The test vector contains a message with a special case hash value.

SpecialK.desc: The test vector contains a message that was constructed such that the value k computed by the derivation from RFC 6979 is an edge case.
SpecialK.effect: Deviating from the correct compuation may leak information about k if an attacker also has access to the expected signature. Such leakage can expose the private key.
